Rescue efforts are continuing, but first we're getting a bulletin of world news.

01:13.490 --> 01:16.990
This is Danielle Yauvetska with the BBC News. Hello.

01:17.750 --> 01:21.670
The Israeli military says its fighter jets, helicopters and artillery

01:21.670 --> 01:25.590
have struck over 500 targets overnight in the Gaza Strip.

01:25.590 --> 01:32.030
Operations are continuing against Palestinian Hamas militants in several locations inside Israel

01:32.030 --> 01:35.650
two days after they carried out their devastating mass assault.

01:36.290 --> 01:38.330
More than 700 Israelis have been killed.

01:38.850 --> 01:40.130
John Donison is in Jerusalem.

01:40.830 --> 01:46.450
The Israeli military says it has continued to target Hamas infrastructure with air strikes overnight.

01:47.030 --> 01:51.690
The United Nations says more than 120,000 gardens have now been displaced

01:51.690 --> 01:54.490
with many seeking shelter in UN schools.

01:54.490 --> 01:57.250
