01:57.730 --> 02:04.070
Israel is massing its forces around Gaza and says it has called up around 100,000 army reservists.

02:04.530 --> 02:07.670
Palestinians are bracing themselves for a possible ground invasion.

02:08.210 --> 02:13.130
With Israel saying its aim is to rescue hostages and remove Hamas from power in Gaza.

02:13.690 --> 02:18.310
Health officials in Gaza say more than 400 Palestinians have been killed so far

02:18.310 --> 02:21.910
by Israeli air strikes. Over 2,000 people have been injured.

02:21.910 --> 02:26.490
They said power cuts were widespread and were posing a major challenge for medical workers.

02:26.910 --> 02:30.070
Hamas said it had fired a new barrage of missiles into Israel.

02:30.630 --> 02:36.610
Three US air carriers as well as Air France, Lufthansa and Emirates have suspended flights to Tel Aviv.

02:37.550 --> 02:41.730
The United States says it is sending immediate extra munitions to Israel.

02:42.010 --> 02:47.550
The Pentagon also announced it was deploying naval vessels including an aircraft carrier to the eastern Mediterranean.

02:48.230 --> 02:50.430
More from Barbara Plattasha in Washington.

02:50.430 --> 02:55.930
The large deployment underscores American concerns that the conflict between Israel and Hamas

02:55.930 --> 02:57.830
could draw in other parts of the region.

02:58.250 --> 03:03.250
They're sending an aircraft carrier with a deck of warplanes accompanied by cruisers and destroyers.

03:03.470 --> 03:05.990
Also extra military assistance such as munitions.

03:06.550 --> 03:11.230
In particular they want to prevent Lebanon's powerful Hezbollah movement from joining the fight.

03:11.510 --> 03:14.810
It's backed by Iran which also funds and arms Hamas.

03:15.350 --> 03:19.070
There are reports that Iran helped organize the unprecedented attack.

03:19.070 --> 03:23.970
Although the Secretary of State Antony Blinken said the US hasn't seen evidence to confirm that.

03:24.830 --> 03:30.070
The UN Security Council has held an emergency closed door session to discuss the crisis.

03:30.790 --> 03:35.870
The UN Middle East envoy called on countries to exert diplomatic efforts to restore calm.

03:36.270 --> 03:38.130
More from Netta Taufiq in New York.

03:38.610 --> 03:41.730
Council members did not attempt to reach agreement on a statement.

03:42.210 --> 03:44.010
Not all but many condemned Hamas.

03:44.010 --> 03:52.430
The UAE's ambassador to the UN, Lana Nusebe, told reporters there was real concern that tensions in the region could become inflamed.

03:52.850 --> 04:00.690
Before the meeting, Israel's ambassador to the UN, Gilad Erdan, showed graphic pictures of Israeli civilians being taken captive by Hamas.

04:01.150 --> 04:08.650
The Palestinian UN ambassador, Riyad Mansour, told reporters he'd requested an emergency meeting of Arab League states in Cairo.

04:09.430 --> 04:11.150
BBC World News.

04:12.330 --> 04:23.770
An independent inquiry in the UK will begin hearings today into allegations that British Special Forces killed dozens of unarmed civilians including children in Afghanistan.

04:24.730 --> 04:29.590
The inquiry was set up by the British government after legal action was brought by two Afghan families.

04:30.950 --> 04:38.010
The US Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, who's leading a bipartisan delegation to China, has met the Foreign Minister Wang Yi.

04:38.010 --> 04:44.130
Mr Schumer is the latest high-level American official to visit as Washington seeks to ease tensions with Beijing.

04:45.550 --> 04:55.070
Regional elections in two of Germany's largest and wealthiest states, Bavaria and Hesse, have dealt a blow to the parties that form the centre-left federal government.

04:55.570 --> 05:00.790
Provisional results show losses for the Social Democrats, the Greens and the Liberal Free Democrats.

05:01.390 --> 05:04.030
The Christian Democrats again emerge as the largest party.

